Biographies



James G. Palumbo


Branch
Email


James G. Palumbo is the founder and principal of Oxford Asset Management, LLC, as well as a Private Wealth Advisor for Oxford’s clients. With 30 years of industry and management experience, Jim has a proven track record of serving clients with excellence. Utilizing the extensive depth of resources at Oxford, Jim’s clients are provided with quality expertise in every area of personal and corporate finance, including estate and retirement planning, tax planning and preparation, and philanthropic counsel. Mr. Palumbo is focused on leading clients towards financial peace of mind through wise and objective counsel. His desire is for his clients to be free to invest their lives in what matters most.
Born in Detroit, Michigan, Mr. Palumbo graduated from Lakeshore High School in 1979 and went directly to Pinecrest Theological Seminary in New York. He went on to found Impact Personal Development Co., a New York consulting firm specializing in management training before bringing his experience to the Financial Services industry and launching Oxford in 1995. He is active in his community and the ministry he founded, EvangAlliance, Inc.






Jose G. Longoria Jr.


Branch
Email


Jose G. Longoria Jr., Investment Advisor Representative, graduated from Roma High School in 1971 and attended Texas A&I University from 1971-1974. Prior to his financial career, Mr. Longoria worked in energy from 1977-1992 with Sunoco and Valero. Mr. Longoria entered the financial industry in 1995 and is registered in Texas with licenses in Life and Health. Joe held his NASD Series 6, 63 and 7 prior to focusing on his Investment Advisory Practice.






Stephen M. Pease
Ph. (970) 375-1291


Branch
Email


Stephen M. Pease, CFP® Professional, and Investment Advisor Representative. He currently holds a Life and Health and Accident license for Colorado and New Mexico. Steve has been investing personally and professionally for 35 years.
Prior to joining Oxford Asset Management, Steve worked for twenty-one years at Mobil Oil Corporation as a geophysicist and technical information manager in production and exploration. His experience spans across a wide range of petroleum and IT projects including: effectively managing multi-million dollar budgets; designing, implementing, and participating in the largest (at the time) 3d seismic survey in Nigeria; and being influential in a highly successful reservoir management project in Indonesia. During his tenure with Mobil, Steve spent more than a decade living and working in Indonesia, Nigeria, Vietnam, and Venezuela gaining invaluable international experience
Steve is a former board President of the Durango Chamber of Commerce. He is also a Durango Chamber of Commerce Diplomat, he is an active member of the La Plata Economic Alliance Business Development Committee, and a Professional Ski Instructors Association (PSIA) certified ski instructor.
Steve received a Bachelor of Science in Geophysical Engineering degree from Colorado School of Mines after graduating from Durango High School in 1975. He is an avid outdoors enthusiast and enjoys golfing (single digit handicap), skiing, scuba diving, sailing, hiking, mountain biking and running.
Steve started in the financial industry in 2003 by purchasing an American General Insurance agency.  He joined Oxford in 2004 as an Investment advisor.  In 2005 Steve passed the series 7 examination.  In early 2006 he started the CFP® certification process and was awarded the Certificate in Jan 2007.






David Smiley
Ph. (970) 375-1291


Branch
Email


David W. Smiley CFP®, RICP®,  joined Oxford Asset Management Durango's office in 2008 as an Investment Advisor Representative. Dave has a Series 65 license (registered as a Uniform Investment Advisor) and maintains his Colorado Life and Health Insurance license.  Dave became a Certified Financial Planner™ professional in 2011 and received his Retirement Income Certified Professional (RICP®) certification in 2014. Dave has been an investor for more than 37 years.
Dave was born and raised in Fort Wayne Indiana. Dave holds a Master of Science degree in Biological Sciences from Illinois State University and a Bachelor of Arts degree in Microbiology from Miami University. Dave moved to the Front Range of Colorado in 1981 where he began his 27 year scientific career.  Dave spent the last 15 years of his scientific career at Amgen, Inc. (a global human therapeutics company in the biotechnology industry). Dave was a senior process development scientist and managed a group that assisted in commercialization activities for several of Amgen's products. His strengths include project management, supervising teams and individuals, problem solving, effective communication, and troubleshooting.
In 2005, Dave began taking classes in the Certified Financial Planning program at Metro State University in Denver while working full time.  With the assistance of his own financial planner and a career coach, he embarked on a new career as a financial planner in 2007. The motivation for the career change was to enable Dave to directly help people make good financial decisions and provide comprehensive financial plans for his clients.
Dave and his wife of 37 years, Gloria, moved to Durango in 2008 to enjoy the area and all its outdoor activities. Dave enjoys reading, hiking, long walks with his golden retriever and Colorado history.  Dave is an active member of the Durango Chamber of Commerce and the Durango Daybreak Rotary club.
 






Jason A. Habbit


Branch
Email


Jason A. Habbit was born and raised in Lafayette, Louisiana. He is a graduate of the University of Louisiana at Lafayette with a degree in Finance. He started his career with Bank One in 2002 and in February of 2005 he moved on to be an independent representative. He has held licenses as a Loan Originator, NASD Series 7 General Securities License, and State of Louisiana Series 66 Uniform Securities License. He currently holds Life & Health insurance licenses for the state of Louisiana.






Terry J. Delhomme, II


Branch
Email


Terry J. Delhomme, II joined Oxford Asset Management as an Investment Advisor Representative in early 2011.  He joined the firm following his departure from the Saint Louis based investment firm Edward Jones where he established and built an office in Acadiana. He has held licenses as a NASD Series 7 General Securities License and State of Louisiana Series 66 Uniform Securities License.  He is designated with Life & Health Insurance licenses for the state of Louisiana.  An avid and enthusiastic supporter of both his community and state, he attended Louisiana State University prior to completing his studies at University of Louisiana at Lafayette with a degree in Finance. Born and raised in Lafayette he actively supports both ULL and LSU athletics, presently serving as a board member for the local chapter of LSU's Tiger Athletic Foundation.






Terry Delhomme


Branch
Email


Terry Delhomme is an Investment Advisor Representative with Oxford Asset Management. Terry was born, raised and educated in Lafayette, Louisiana. He is a 1980 graduate of the University of Louisiana at Lafayette with a Bachelor's in Business Administration, with a major in Accounting. He is a licensed agent in Louisiana for Life and Health Insurance, and currently holds a NASD Series 6 and State of Louisiana Series 65 Uniform Securities License. Terry is also a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) and serves as Managing Partner of the Lafayette based accounting firm of Delhomme, McDowell, and Associates, LLC. He is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants and the Louisiana State Society of CPA's.






David Varisco


Branch
Email


David Varisco is an Investment Advisor Representative with Oxford. He earned his LUTCF designation in 1995, and is a lifelong resident of Lafayette. In 1989 he established his insurance and investment practice; his son Brandon joined in 2008. He is the past president of the Acadiana Association of Health Underwriters and NAIFA Acadiana, was named Health Insurance Agent of the year in 1992 and is well known for being a founding member of the Cajun Rock group Atchafalaya as well as the mascot for the Louisiana Icegators Hockey Team and is the drummer for Lafayette's Bayou Boys and Full Circle.






Brandon Varisco


Branch
Email


Brandon Varisco is an Investment Adviser Representative with Oxford. He graduated from the University Of Phoenix with a Bachelor degree in Business and Finance in 2012. He currently holds a series 65 Uniform Securities License, and is a licensed agent in Louisiana for Life and Health Insurance. He joined Oxford in 2008 after over six years of active duty military service as a paratrooper with the U.S. Army’s 82nd Airborne Division. A few of his military accomplishments and awards include: over 1000 flight hours as a crew-chief, mechanic and door gunner on the UH60 Black hawk helicopter; 500 of which are combat flight hours. He is a graduate of both U.S. Army Airborne School, and Aviation Life Support Equipment Repairer School. Brandon served tours in both Iraq (2003) and Afghanistan (2007). While deployed he was awarded the Army Combat Action Badge, 4 Air Medals, one of which was awarded with a V device for Valor in combat. He was honorably discharged in May of 2008.






Scott Rader


Branch
Email


Born in Reading, Pennsylvania Scott brings decades of experience as a bilingual manager of US Company facilities in Mexico, small business owner, and financial advisor at Edward Jones, to his new position as Manager, and Investment Advisor Representative for Oxford’s Central Texas offices in San Antonio and Boerne. We came to know Scott and Karen shortly after they adopted their children and served as Minister of Adult Education and Missions at our home church, Calvary Baptist in McAllen, Texas. Their selflessness is an inspiration to us and a great example of the Servant Leader philosophy to which Oxford is committed.














