About Us | Oxford Asset Management









































About Us
Our team of mathematicians, scientists, computer scientists and software engineers have developed proprietary algorithms and trading software to invest on a global scale.







The Firm
OxFORD Asset Management® is an investment manager based in Oxford, UK.
Since launch in 2004, our team of mathematicians, scientists, computer scientists and software engineers have developed proprietary algorithms and trading software to invest on a global scale. Many of us invest alongside our clients.
What we do
We apply computational models to financial markets, analysing a range of data and information, and exploiting relationships among financial instruments such as stocks, futures, and currencies. Most trading of the fund’s portfolio is managed automatically by our proprietary algorithms and software. Our team works with the latest technologies to develop these algorithms and tools to navigate a wide range of markets.


The Team
Our team of over 80 comprises:

Researchers, who identify opportunities and build our quantitative models and strategies.
Computer Scientists & Software Engineers, who design the software that drives our investment strategies.
Computing Infrastructure Specialists, who design and support our trading and business infrastructure.
Our Operational Team supports our investment professionals and clients.

How we work
We tackle real-world problems with an open mind, and draw inspiration from a vast array of sources. We place huge value on clear thinking that leads to elegant solutions. We encourage a culture of innovation and craftsmanship, and embrace a philosophy of continual improvement. With release cycles measured in hours, there is immediate feedback on personal contribution.


The Events
As part of our commitment to fostering a sociable working environment, we hold a range of events throughout the year. We have recently held a summer BBQ at the botanical garden, a private museum tour, and a conference at a country retreat.
















 




Our Offices | Oxford Asset Management









































Our Offices
We foster an interactive and sociable working environment.







Our offices are in the heart of Oxford city centre, surrounded by the renowned University of Oxford and its Colleges. We have bespoke high-specification facilities, supported by state of the art communication and technology systems.
The space is designed to foster an interactive working environment between teams. We enjoy socialising – lunch is in our Refectory, and we have a dedicated lecture theatre for training and events, as well as special lunchtime talks.
We prioritise a comfortable work environment, which is why you’ll find break-out zones, coffee machines, pick and mix boxes, and healthy snack stands at every turn. For those commuting to work by bike, or fancying a run at lunchtime, there are showers and changing facilities.


















 




Careers | Oxford Asset Management









































Careers
We are always looking for exceptionally talented individuals who are ambitious and relish a challenge.







Working at OxFORD Asset Management
We are always looking for exceptionally talented individuals who are ambitious and relish a challenge. We value mental flexibility, innovative thinking, and the ability to work collaboratively. Teamwork is as important to us as individual excellence. A background in finance is not necessary.
We are looking for an advanced degree in mathematics, computer science, physics or econometrics, although we will consider highly numerate graduate applicants.
Our team is friendly and intelligent, and from a wide range of backgrounds. We come to work in jeans, rather than suits. We are a collegiate group, with a flat management structure and no silos.
OxFORD offers a comprehensive and flexible benefits package, including competitive salary and performance related bonus, private healthcare, pension, life assurance and long term disability cover.
For general recruitment queries, please contact us at recruitment@oxam.com


Work With Us
Computing Infrastructure SpecialistsWe are seeking graduate-level to highly experienced computing infrastructure specialists, to assist with the design, implementation and support of our firm-wide IT Infrastructure.More detailsComputer Scientists & Software EngineersWe are seeking outstanding computer scientists and software engineers to help design and implement our quantitative models and trading systems.More detailsResearchersWe are seeking outstanding researchers to build quantitative models of financial markets.More detailsInternshipsWe are seeking undergraduates, graduates and doctoral students to join our internship programmes. These range from several weeks, to one year placements, and cover the areas of Software Engineering, Quantitative Research, Data Analysis and Systems Infrastructure.More details


















