Oxford Asset Management Trimmed By $4.28 Million Its Exelixis (EXEL) Stake, 9 Analysts Bullish BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (BHP)


					
						July 27, 2017 - By Vivian Currie

Among 24 analysts covering BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (NYSE:BHP), 9 have Buy rating, 3 Sell and 12 Hold. Therefore 38% are positive. BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) had 50 analyst reports since July 22, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. Morgan Stanley upgraded BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (NYSE:BHP) on Wednesday, January 13 to “Overweight” rating. RBC Capital Markets upgraded the stock to “Sector Perform” rating in Wednesday, August 26 report. The stock has “Underperform” rating by BNP Paribas on Thursday, August 27. The stock has “Sell” rating by Liberum Capital on Thursday, October 29. The rating was maintained by Cowen & Co with “Hold” on Thursday, July 13. The firm has “Hold” rating by Argus Research given on Wednesday, March 9. The firm earned “Hold” rating on Friday, July 14 by HSBC. The firm has “Hold” rating given on Thursday, December 1 by Argus Research. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Tuesday, August 4 by JP Morgan. The stock of BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (NYSE:BHP) has “Underweight” rating given on Tuesday, January 12 by Barclays Capital. See BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (NYSE:BHP) latest ratings:







19/07/2017 Broker: Citigroup Rating: Hold Downgrade13/07/2017 Broker: Cowen & Co Rating: Hold New Target: $40.0000 Maintain14/07/2017 Broker: HSBC Rating: Hold Downgrade05/07/2017 Broker: Deutsche Bank Rating: Buy Upgrade27/06/2017 Broker: Argus Research Rating: Buy New Target: $46.0000 08/06/2017 Broker: Jefferies Rating: Hold Downgrade05/07/2017 Broker: Bernstein Old Rating: Market Perform New Rating: Outperform Upgrade07/04/2017 Broker: CLSA Old Rating: Outperform New Rating: Buy Upgrade17/03/2017 Broker: Investec Old Rating: Hold New Rating: Buy Upgrade
Oxford Asset Management decreased Exelixis Inc (EXEL) stake by 74.34% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Oxford Asset Management sold 305,943 shares as Exelixis Inc (EXEL)’s stock declined 14.88%. The Oxford Asset Management holds 105,607 shares with $1.58 million value, down from 411,550 last quarter. Exelixis Inc now has $8.18 billion valuation. The stock declined 0.14% or $0.04 reaching $27.98 per share. About 732,354 shares traded. Exelixis, Inc. (NASDAQ:EXEL) has risen 266.48% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 249.78% the S&P500.
BHP Billiton Limited is a global resources company. The company has market cap of $102.26 billion. The Firm is a producer of various commodities, including iron ore, metallurgical coal, copper and uranium. It has a 43.91 P/E ratio. The Company’s divisions include Petroleum, Copper, Iron Ore and Coal.
 About 818,133 shares traded. BHP Billiton Limited (ADR) (NYSE:BHP) has risen 34.32% since July 27, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 17.62% the S&P500.
Since February 1, 2017, it had 0 insider buys, and 22 selling transactions for $28.28 million activity. Hessekiel Jeffrey had sold 23,787 shares worth $488,585. The insider FELDBAUM CARL B sold 10,000 shares worth $217,700. Shares for $218,200 were sold by COHEN CHARLES on Monday, March 13. WYSZOMIERSKI JACK L had sold 5,150 shares worth $111,086 on Friday, March 31. On Monday, May 1 the insider Schwab Gisela sold $2.07 million. $4.54 million worth of stock was sold by MORRISSEY MICHAEL on Friday, March 3. MARCHESI VINCENT T sold $213,000 worth of stock.
Among 9 analysts covering Exelixis (NASDAQ:EXEL), 7 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 78% are positive. Exelixis had 17 analyst reports since January 19, 2016 according to SRatingsIntel. Oppenheimer maintained the shares of EXEL in report on Monday, June 5 with “Hold” rating. The stock of Exelixis, Inc. (NASDAQ:EXEL) earned “Hold” rating by Stifel Nicolaus on Tuesday, February 28. As per Thursday, July 20, the company rating was maintained by Oppenheimer. The stock of Exelixis, Inc. (NASDAQ:EXEL) earned “Hold” rating by Oppenheimer on Monday, June 19. Stifel Nicolaus maintained Exelixis, Inc. (NASDAQ:EXEL) rating on Thursday, September 15. Stifel Nicolaus has “Buy” rating and $15 target. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Friday, July 21 by J.P. Morgan. Deutsche Bank initiated it with “Buy” rating and $17 target in Thursday, November 3 report. Stifel Nicolaus upgraded the shares of EXEL in report on Monday, April 4 to “Buy” rating. SunTrust initiated the shares of EXEL in report on Thursday, July 13 with “Buy” rating. Oppenheimer initiated the stock with “Hold” rating in Monday, June 12 report.
Analysts await Exelixis, Inc. (NASDAQ:EXEL) to report earnings on August, 2 after the close. They expect $0.03 EPS, up 118.75% or $0.19 from last year’s $-0.16 per share. EXEL’s profit will be $8.77 million for 233.17 P/E if the $0.03 EPS becomes a reality. After $0.05 actual EPS reported by Exelixis, Inc. for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -40.00% negative EPS growth. 








