As Brf Sa (BRFS) Share Price Declined, Oxford Asset Management Has Cut Holding by $10.35 Million


					

						July 13, 2017 - By Maria Brooks

Oxford Asset Management decreased its stake in Brf Sa (BRFS) by 39.83% based on its latest 2016Q4 regulatory filing with the SEC. Oxford Asset Management sold 739,172 shares as the company’s stock declined 10.72% while stock markets rallied. The hedge fund held 1.12 million shares of the meat and poultry and fish company at the end of 2016Q4, valued at $16.48M, down from 1.86M at the end of the previous reported quarter. Oxford Asset Management who had been investing in Brf Sa for a number of months, seems to be less bullish one the $10.15 billion market cap company. The stock rose 0.93% or $0.11 reaching $11.99. About 879,078 shares traded. BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) has declined 2.88% since July 13, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 19.58% the S&P500.






Oxford Asset Management, which manages about $13.99B and $2.01 billion US Long portfolio, upped its stake in Cloud Peak Energy Inc (NYSE:CLD) by 990,592 shares to 1.22 million shares, valued at $6.85M in 2016Q4, according to the filing. It also increased its holding in Imperva Inc (NYSE:IMPV) by 139,251 shares in the quarter, for a total of 551,386 shares, and has risen its stake in Gulfport Energy Corp (NASDAQ:GPOR). 
More notable recent BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) news were published by: Investorplace.com which released: “Why BRF SA (ADR) (BRFS), Snap Inc (SNAP) and Amgen, Inc. (AMGN) Are 3 of Today …” on March 17, 2017, also Benzinga.com with their article: “Is Brazil’s Investment Climate Improving? BRF SA Stands To Benefit” published on July 19, 2016, Seekingalpha.com published: “2 Rotten Meat And Deforestation Scandals Impact JBS’s And BRF’s USD 2.5 …” on April 03, 2017. More interesting news about BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) were released by: Seekingalpha.com and their article: “BRF’s Operating Margin May Limit Free Cash Flow Growth” published on December 15, 2015 as well as Marketwatch.com‘s news article titled: “11.44” with publication date: December 22, 2009.
BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) Ratings Coverage
Among 6 analysts covering BRF S.A. (NYSE:BRFS), 3 have Buy rating, 1 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. BRF S.A. had 10 analyst reports since September 16, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was downgraded by Bank of America on Friday, October 30 to “Neutral”. The firm earned “Neutral” rating on Wednesday, September 16 by JP Morgan. The firm has “Neutral” rating given on Monday, January 9 by JP Morgan. The stock of BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) earned “Sell” rating by Goldman Sachs on Monday, October 5. Deutsche Bank upgraded BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) on Friday, January 29 to “Buy” rating. The stock has “Buy” rating by Citigroup on Thursday, October 8. The rating was upgraded by JP Morgan on Tuesday, May 31 to “Overweight”. Bank of America maintained BRF SA (ADR) (NYSE:BRFS) on Friday, May 26 with “Buy” rating.


